<div id="what" class="site-wrapper">
	<div class="site-wrapper-inner">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>
				Εxodus is an audit plateform for Android applications.
			</h1>
			<h2>
				It detects behaviors which can be dangerous for user privacy.<br>
				Ads, tracking, analytics…
			</h2>
			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-7">
					<h2>
						Comprehensive reports
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus provides a report for each analyzed application.<br/>
						Reports show the list of detected trackers, permissions
						and suspicious network traffic.<br/>
						Exodus also offers a brief description of each tracker
						is is able to detect.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<%= image_tag 'report.png', class: %i[featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto] %>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
					<%= image_tag 'trackers.png', class: %i[featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto] %>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
					<h2>
						Static analysis
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus is able to detect presence of tracker code
						directly in the APK file without requiring decompilation.<br/>
						Exodus bases its analysis on APK files downloaded from
						Google Play.<br/>
						It ensures that Exodus analyzes applications which are
						available for any other user.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr/>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-7">
					<h2>
						Network analysis
					</h2>
					<p class="lead">
						Exodus executes the application and then dumps the
						entire network traffic generated by the simulated
						Android device.<br/>
						Exodus analyzes DNS, UDP, HTTP and HTTPS traffic to
						determine the collected data and the destination server.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<%= image_tag 'network.png', class: %i[featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto] %>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

